            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate to restore programmatic stability and ensure the U.S. maintains its strategic lead against rising competition from China.\n* Support local FL-14 research at The University of Tampa, which holds active NASA grants for gamma-ray burst citizen science and lunar/Martian exploration initiatives.\n* Drive regional economic growth through contracts with local firms like American Wordata, Inc., which sustains critical data storage infrastructure for NASA missions.\n* Leverage a 3:1 economic return on investment to protect the high-tech workforce and STEM talent pipeline across the aerospace and technology sectors.",
